Anne,<br><br>
You have wisdom beyond your years, now matter how old you are.  I wish all people who visit this site read your words, and know these were difficult times for all of us<br><br>
I can picture your father in my mind, standing there, watching your mom.  He must have been as proud of your mom as she was of him and both of them for the soldiers who went to war.<br><br>
Your honesty is appreciated.  You did not mince your deep felt thoughts.  I commend you.  I don't know if this will help your and your man or not.  Read the last post on thread #48, that's me.  My alter ego is still married to the same woman, for more than thirty years.  I have been married and divorced twice.  I do not believe Vietnam was a factor in eihter divorce, but you might want to tell him that it is probably easier to be me than him.  He is a good man, I'm not really sure,  I haven't seen him since 1967, but he/they raised four daughters.  Tell your guy to hang on and work on &quot;it,&quot; I'm sure you both deserve each other.<br><br>
Paul
